  "summary": "Malicious code in slow-surf (npm)",
  "details": "Slow-surf@10.0.0 runs a preinstall hook (node notify.js) that collects system information — hostname, username, current working directory, NODE_ENV, and CPU architecture — and exfiltrates it via HTTPS POST to webhook[.]site/4d0cc13d-a185-4e95-92dc-f4681125055c. The payload is a host-metadata beacon that fingerprints the installation environment.",
